
=============================
    FULL GIT COMMAND GUIDE
=============================

This file includes commands for:
- Pushing code/files to main
- Pushing files to branches (dev1/dev2)
- Cloning, committing, pulling, and merging
- One-liners for quick use

=============================
ğŸ“¦ CLONE REPOSITORY (First Time)
=============================
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
cd your-repo

=============================
ğŸŒ¿ WORKING ON MAIN BRANCH
=============================

âœ… Switch to main branch:
git checkout main

âœ… Add a new file (e.g., notes.txt):
git add notes.txt

âœ… Commit changes:
git commit -m "Added notes.txt"

âœ… Push to main branch:
git push origin main

âœ… ğŸ” One-liner:
git checkout main && git add notes.txt && git commit -m "Added notes.txt" && git push origin main

âœ… Push all files in project to main:
git add .
git commit -m "Updated full project"
git push origin main

=============================
ğŸŒ¿ WORKING ON BRANCHES (dev1 / dev2)
=============================

âœ… Create and switch to a branch:
git checkout -b dev1        # or dev2

âœ… Switch to existing branch:
git checkout dev1           # or dev2

âœ… Add specific file (e.g., demo.txt):
git add demo.txt

âœ… Or add all files:
git add .

âœ… Commit your changes:
git commit -m "Updated demo.txt"

âœ… Push to your branch:
git push origin dev1        # or dev2

âœ… Pull latest updates from branch:
git pull origin dev1        # or dev2

âœ… ğŸ” One-liner:
git add . && git commit -m "Updated files" && git push origin dev1   # or dev2

=============================
ğŸ” MERGING TO MAIN (After Review)
=============================

âœ… On GitHub:
- Create Pull Request from dev1 or dev2 to main
- Review and Merge

âœ… Then update local main:
git checkout main
git pull origin main

=============================
ğŸ§¼ OPTIONAL CLEANUP
=============================

âœ… Delete a merged branch (locally):
